  Option 2: Pine Script Screener (Best for Watchlist)

  Create a screener that monitors multiple symbols:

  //@version=5
  indicator("Watchlist Screener", overlay=false)

  // Define your watchlist
  var string[] watchlist = array.from("AAPL", "TSLA", "NVDA", "MSFT", "GOOGL")

  // Your alert condition
  rsiValue = ta.rsi(close, 14)
  isOverbought = rsiValue > 70

  if isOverbought
      alert('{"content": "ðŸ”´ ' + syminfo.ticker + ' OVERBOUGHT at ' + str.tostring(close) + '"}', alert.freq_once_per_bar)

  Then set one alert on this indicator with "Any alert() function call" - it monitors the current chart but you can duplicate
  across watchlist charts.

